---
import Article from "../../../layouts/Article.astro";
import KeyTakeaway from "../../../components/KeyTakeaway.astro";
import InfoBox from "../../../components/InfoBox.astro";
---

<Article
  title="Scythe Faction Tier List: Which Faction Is Best?"
  description="Ranking all 5 base game factions by strength, ease of play, and optimal strategy."
  game="scythe"
  gameTitle="Scythe"
  category="Strategy"
  publishDate="2025-05-06"
>
  <p>
    Scythe's 5 base factions play very differently. Some reward aggression,
    others reward engine building. Here's how they stack up — and what matters
    more than the faction itself.
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaway answer="Crimea and Rusviet are generally the strongest base factions. Nordic is the easiest for beginners. But your player mat matters more than your faction — the faction/mat combination determines your game, not the faction alone." />

  <div class="my-8 space-y-6">
    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-emerald-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">S TIER</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🐻</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Rusviet Union</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">Faction Ability: Relentless</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-red-50 text-red-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Aggressive</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-purple-50 text-purple-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Flexible</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Can repeat the same action space on consecutive turns — an enormous tempo advantage.
        While other factions zigzag between actions, Rusviet can hammer one strategy relentlessly.
        Central starting position gives easy access to the Factory.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-emerald-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">S TIER</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🏇</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Crimean Khanate</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">Faction Ability: Coercion</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Versatile</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Combat Cards as Resources</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Can use combat cards as any resource once per turn. This flexibility means you never
        get stuck without the right resource. Strong combat potential thanks to mech abilities
        and good starting position near the Factory.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-blue-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">A TIER</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🦅</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Saxony Empire</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">Faction Ability: Dominate</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-red-50 text-red-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Warlike</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Unlimited Combat Stars</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        No limit on combat victory stars (other factions cap at 2). Can also achieve unlimited
        objective stars. This means Saxony can rush to 6 stars through fighting — but it
        requires careful power and popularity management.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-blue-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">A TIER</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">⚙️</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Polania Republic</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">Faction Ability: Meander</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Encounter-Focused</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Flexible</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Picks from 2 options (instead of 1) on encounter cards. This gives consistently better
        encounter rewards. Great at accumulating resources and popularity through encounters.
        Requires good movement planning to maximize encounters early.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-gray-400 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">B TIER</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">❄️</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Nordic Kingdoms</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">Faction Ability: Swim</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Beginner-Friendly</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Water Movement</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Workers can swim across rivers without mechs. Simple to play and great for learning
        the game, but the ability becomes less impactful as you get better at planning mech
        deployment. Isolated starting position limits early Factory access.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <InfoBox type="warning" title="Player Mat Matters More">
    The faction/player mat combination determines your strength, not the faction alone. A "weak" faction with the Industrial or Engineering mat can outperform a "strong" faction with a poor mat pairing. If you're playing with random assignment, focus on optimizing your mat's action economy.
  </InfoBox>

  <InfoBox type="tip" title="For New Players">
    Start with Nordic — the swim ability removes the biggest stumbling block for beginners (figuring out when to deploy mechs for river crossing). Once comfortable, try Crimea for a more strategic experience.
  </InfoBox>
</Article>
